Lagos – Plateau and Osun states paid the highest average price of premium motor spirit (petrol) in the month of February 2018, according to the current report of the Nigerian Bureau of Statistics (NBS). Both states paid N206.82 per litre and N201.29per litre respectively, while Edo state paid N200.83 per litre on the product during the period in view. According to the report, states with the lowest average price of premium motor spirit (petrol) were Katsina (N145.00), Abuja (N145.00) and Kogi (N147.06). It added that average price paid by consumers for premium motor spirit (petrol) increased by 15.1% year-on-year and -9.6% Month-on-Month to N172.5 in February 2018 from N190.9 in January 2018. It said that average price paid by consumers for automotive gas oil (diesel) decreased by 1.84% month-on-month and -15.84% year-on-year to N209.89 in February 2018 from N213.82 in January 2018. The report added that states with the highest average price of diesel were Sokoto (N264.00), Yobe (N238.00) and Taraba (N232.00) It said states with the lowest average price of diesel were Ogun (N190.63), Ondo (N190.00) and Abia (N190.00). The NBS report also stated that average price per litre paid by consumers for National Household Kerosene decreased by -0.10% month-on-month and decreased by -18.12% year-on-year to N288.57 in February 2018 from N288.85 in January 2018. According to the report, states with the highest average price per litre of kerosene were Plateau (N319.44), Nassarawa (N316.67) and Bayelsa (N315.28). It added that states with the lowest average price per litre of kerosene were Kebbi (N257.29), Oyo (N260.53) and Niger (N262.5) “Similarly, average price per gallon paid by consumers for National Household Kerosene increased by 0.54% month-on-month and decreased by -24.58% year-on-year to N1,030.33 in February 2018 from N1,024.83 in January 2018,” it added. According to the report, average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) decreased by -1.56% month-on-month and decreased by -20.40% year-on-year to N2155.97 in February 2018 from N2,190.07 in January 2018. It added that states with the highest average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) were Borno (N2500.00), Yobe (N2500.00), and Anambra (N2364.29). States with the lowest average price for the refilling of a 5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) were Abuja (N1,820.00), Ebonyi (N1,860.00) and Ekiti (N1,950.00). It said similarly, average price for the refilling of a 12.5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) increased by 0.12% month-on-month and decreased by -18.94% year-on-year to N4333.27 in February 2018 from N4,327.89 in January 2018. According to the report, states with the highest average price for the refilling of a 12.5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) were Akwa Ibom (N5,000.00), Benue (N5,000.00) and Kogi (N4,816.67). It added that states with the lowest average price for the refilling of a 12.5kg cylinder for Liquefied Petroleum Gas (Cooking Gas) were Oyo (N3871.05), Ogun (N3788.89) and Lagos (N3,727.78). 0 comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE.  100% Natural Solution To Premature Ejaculation, Weak Erection, Watery Sperm, Other Sexual Dysfunctions And Last More Than 30 Minutes During Sex.